ex, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"31 January 1592–       1650":"31 januari 1592–1650","1592–Male":"1592–Overleden","1616–1659":"1616–1659","1592–1650":"1592–1650","1600":"1600","       1650":"1650","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1651":"1651","1650":"1650","1592":"1592","31 January 1592":"31 januari 1592","before 1616":"vóór 1616","1616":"1616","1659":"1659","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Harwich, Essex, England":"Harwich, Essex, England","London, England":"London, England","Harwich, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Harwich, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"31 January 1592–       1650":"31 January 1592–1650","1592–Male":"1592–Deceased","1616–1659":"1616–1659","1592–1650":"1592–1650","1600":"1600","       1650":"1650","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1651":"1651","1650":"1650","1592":"1592","31 January 1592":"31 January 1592","before 1616":"before 1616","1616":"1616","1659":"1659","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Harwich, Essex, England":"Harwich, Essex, England","London, England":"London, England","Harwich, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Harwich, Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Gray","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish (especially Eastern Ulster; of Norman origin): habitational name from Graye in Calvados, France, named from the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Graec(i)us</i>, meaning ‘Greek’ + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>. This is probably the chief source of the surname in Britain.","English: nickname for someone with gray hair or a gray beard, from Middle English <i>grey</i> (Old English <i>grǣg</i>, <i>grēg</i>) ‘gray’. In Ireland it has been used as a translation of various Gaelic surnames derived from <i>riabhach</i> ‘brindled, gray’, including <b>Mac Giolla Riabhaigh</b>; see   McGreevy  . In North America, this surname has assimilated names with similar meaning from other languages.","French: habitational name from Gray in Haute-Saône or Le Gray in Seine-Maritime."],"variants":[{"name":"McGreevy","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Seamus, Brendan.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mag Riabhaigh</b>, a patronymic from the personal name <i>Riabhach</i> ‘brindled, grizzled’. Compare   Reavey   and   Creevy   2."]},{"name":"Grayer","meanings":["English (southern): nickname from Middle English <i>grei</i> ‘gray’ (see   Gray  ) + <i>her</i> ‘hair’.","Scottish (Ayrshire): variant of   Greer  ."]},{"name":"Grays","meanings":["English (Durham): variant of   Gray  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>, or of   Grace  ."]},{"name":"Grice","meanings":["English (Midlands): from Middle English <i>grice</i>, <i>grise</i> ‘pig’ (Old Norse <i>gríss</i>), probably a nickname or a metonymic occupational name for a swineherd.","English: nickname for a gray-haired man, from Middle English <i>grice</i>, <i>gris</i> ‘gray’ (Old French <i>gris</i>, apparently of ancient Germanic origin, and probably a distant cognate of   Gray   1).","Possibly also an Americanized form of German   Greis  ."]},{"name":"Grey","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Irish: variant of   Gray  .","German: dialect variant of   Grau  .","In some cases also an American shortened and altered form of Ukrainian <b>Grushko</b>: nickname or topographic name derived from a Russian-influenced transliteration of <i>grushka</i> ‘pear, pear tree’."]}]},{"name":"Susan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["vernacular form of   Susanna .  Among well-known bearers are the American film stars  Susan Hayward  (  1918–75 ) and  Susan Sarandon  (  b. 1946  as  Susan Tomalin )."],"variants":[{"name":"Suzan","meanings":["vernacular form of   Susanna .  Among well-known bearers are the American film stars  Susan Hayward  (  1918–75 ) and  Susan Sarandon  (  b. 1946  as  Susan Tomalin )."]},{"name":"Susanna","meanings":["New Testament form (Luke 8:3) of the Hebrew name <i>Shoshana</i> (from <i>shoshan</i> ‘lily’, which in modern Hebrew also means ‘rose’)."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705210,"age":7,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":27,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705213,"age":49,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Susan Gray was born on 31 January 1592, in Harwich, Essex, England. She married Emanuel Eglesfield before 1616, in Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1650, at the age of 58."},"et":{"31 January 1592–       1650":"31. jaanuar 1592–1650","1592–Male":"1592–Surnud","1616–1659":"1616–1659","1592–1650":"1592–1650","1600":"1600","       1650":"1650","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1651":"1651","1650":"1650","1592":"1592","31 January 1592":"31. jaanuar 1592","before 1616":"enne 1616","1616":"1616","1659":"1659","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Harwich, Essex, England":"Harwich, Essex, England","London, England":"London, England","Harwich, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Harwich, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"31 January 1592–       1650":"31. tammikuuta 1592–1650","1592–Male":"1592–Kuollut","1616–1659":"1616–1659","1592–1650":"1592–1650","1600":"1600","       1650":"1650","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1651":"1651","1650":"1650","1592":"1592","31 January 1592":"31. tammikuuta 1592","before 1616":"ennen vuotta 1616","1616":"1616","1659":"1659","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Harwich, Essex, England":"Harwich, Essex, England","London, England":"London, England","Harwich, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Harwich, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"31 January 1592–       1650":"31 janvier 1592–1650","1592–Male":"1592–Décédé","1616–1659":"1616–1659","1592–1650":"1592–1650","1600":"1600","       1650":"1650","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1651":"1651","1650":"1650","1592":"1592","31 January 1592":"31 janvier 1592","before 1616":"avant 1616","1616":"1616","1659":"1659","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Angleterre","Harwich, Essex, England":"Harwich, Essex, Angleterre","London, England":"Londres, Angleterre","Harwich, Essex, England, United Kingdom":"Harwich, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Susan Gray est née le 31 janvier 1592, à Harwich, Essex, Angleterre. Elle a épousé Emanuel Eglesfield avant 1616, à Somerset, A